56 objects using disk\nPage Caching using disk: enhanced (Page is feed) \nLazy Loading (feed)\nDatabase Caching using disk (Request-wide modification query)\n\nServed from: domain.com @ 2022-09-15 15:39:36 by W3 Total Cache\n--&gt;</code></pre>\n<p>I have two questions:</p>\n<p>1. For Page Cache I have the caching of Feeds unchecked. Is this still expected behavior?</p>\n<p>2. Is it recommended to cache feeds in general? It feels like this doesn&#8217;t help when it comes to having them as recent as possible or do I get that wrong? Should I check the caching for feeds in Page Cache / does it make a difference regarding above quoted appendix?</p>\n<p>Thanks and best regards,<br />\neC</p>\n						\n					\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n					\n				\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:107:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/after-plugin-activated-deactivated-page-cache-clearing-is-not-reliable/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"After plugin activated/deactivated, page cache clearing is not reliable\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:107:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/after-plugin-activated-deactivated-page-cache-clearing-is-not-reliable/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 14 Sep 2022 08:06:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3203:\"\n						\n						<p>Replies: 2</p>\n						<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>I am Yuvaraj, developer at WPCal. We have many common users.<br />\nWe are having a couple of issues with the W3 total cache all those looks like common issues, they can happen to any other plugin.</p>\n<p>We use a shortcode added to WP pages for our booking functionality.</p>\n<p>Problem 1)<br />\nYour plugin gives the following notice whenever a plugin is activated or deactivated.</p>\n<blockquote><p>&#8220;One or more plugins have been activated or deactivated, please empty the page cache and check the minify settings to maintain the desired user experience.&#8221;</p></blockquote>\n<p>But your plugin only displays the notice on the WP Plugins page and W3 Total Cache settings page.<br />\nAs soon as our plugin is activated, it redirects to one of our pages, and the notice is not displayed. That user faces an issue with my plugin as the shortcode is not working.</p>\n<p>Problem 2)<br />\n<strong>Steps</strong><br />\n1. My plugin activated, and all cache cleared<br />\n2. It has a page with a shortcode<br />\n3. The same page is loaded in 2 browser tabs(all works).<br />\n4. My plugin is deactivated<br />\n5. As per your notice, I am clearing the page cache from the notice.</p>\n<p>Observed:<br />\nTab 1: Reloaded &#8211; Displaying shortcode as a text. Perfect. But trying the same steps a few times with Browser Dev tools cache disabled, sometimes it shows the functionality instead of the shortcode as a text #SporadicBug.</p>\n<p>Tab 2: Not reloaded &#8211; But when ajax functionality is triggered with a button, it works as though the plugin is activated. I checked it with PHP Xdebug, my plugin files are included in runtime and codes are executed even after the plugin is deactivated #Bug.<br />\nThen I found the issue is object caching. So whenever a plugin is activated/deactivated object cache also needs to be cleared along with the page cache.<br />\nOnly after clearing the object cache, I get 400 bad request errors for my ajax calls which is perfect.</p>\n<p>I am not facing this issue with any other cache plugin we tested. I think most plugins automatically clear all, or required cache after a plugin is activated/deactivated.</p>\n<p>I request you to implement the following, or even better solutions are welcome.<br />\nOption 1 (Best in terms of reliability): The best solution is Clear all the cache whenever one or more plugins are activated/deactivated for more reliability.</p>\n<p>Option 2: At least show the notice in all the admin end pages along with the option to clear all cache or page/object/DB or whatever applies.</p>\n<p>As option 1 is an automatic option, I believe your user will enjoy it (one less thing to do), and it works reliably. </p>\n<p>Looking forward to your reply.</p>\n\n\n<ul id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-16007942\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log\">\n\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-16007942-item-16007953\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 4 days, 4 hours ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/yuvarajsenthil/\" title=\"View Yuvaraj Senthil&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">Yuvaraj Senthil</span></a>.\n	</li>\n\n</ul>\n\n						\n					\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Yuvaraj Senthil\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n					\n				\";s:7: