 have tried all the possible solutions to speed up my website but the mobile page speed result is still low.<br />\nI am thinking of adding one more cache plugin called W3 Total Cache.<br />\nRight now Enabled Auto Minify, Brotli, and Rocket Loader on Cloudflare.<br />\nCSS and JS cache is happening Autoptimize. The HTML page cache in Cloudflare.</p>\n<p>I installed W3 Total Cache and made the following changes<br />\n1. Enabled page cache<br />\n2. Enabled Minify<br />\n3. Opcode Cache: Zend Opcode<br />\n4. Enabled Database Cache<br />\n5. Enabled Object Cache<br />\n6. Enabled Browser Cache<br />\n7. Enabled Lazy Load Images<br />\n8. Enabled Google Page Speed dashboard widget<br />\n9. Verify rewrite rules<br />\n10. Optimize disk enhanced page and minify disk caching for NFS</p>\n<p>After the changes, all the plugins got diactivated and I had to set up the plugins from scratch<br />\nCan&#8217;t we use W3 Total Cache + Autoptimize together?<br />\nwhat are all the changes I need to make here?<br />\nIs it a good idea to use Cloudflare + W3 Total Cache + Autoptimize plugins altogether?</p>\n<p>any help would be helpful<br />\nThank you!`</p>\n						\n					\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"chandana1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:21;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n					\n				\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/cache-of-listing-grid-for-logged-in-user/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:5:\"ti